# Performance

## Route-level code splitting

New pages must use `React.lazy` + `Suspense` in `App.tsx`. Avoid adding eager page imports — the current `App.tsx` eagerly loads all pages and should be migrated incrementally.

## Memoization

- Filter/sort/map large lists: wrap in `React.useMemo` with correct deps
- Stable callbacks passed to children: `React.useCallback`
- List items: stable `key` (entity `id`, not array index)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const filtered = React.useMemo(() => filterHeroes(heroes, filters), [heroes, filters])

// ❌ BAD — recomputes every render
const filtered = filterHeroes(heroes, filters)
```

## Images

- Content images: `loading="lazy"` and explicit `width`/`height` when possible
- Hero portraits: avoid loading full-resolution assets in list grids

## Avoid render-time heavy work

Move expensive calculations to `useMemo`, utils in `src/lib/`, or precompute in `DataContext`. Never run O(n²) loops inline in JSX for large datasets.

## Charts (recharts)

Limit data points passed to charts. Memoize chart data transformations.
